Explain how specific properties of different forms of seismic waves contribute to our understanding of the characteristics and dimensions of Earth's interior layers.\
There are generally two types of seismic waves, which are energy waves caused by earthquakes. Seismic waves can contribute to our understanding of the characteristics and dimensions of Earth and it\'92s interior layers because they can behave in different ways dependent upon what type of wave they are. P-waves are faster (shorter), and can travel through both solids and liquids, while S-waves are slower (longer), and can only traverse solids. Both kind of waves travel differently depending on the material they are penetrating. By measuring the arrival of seismic waves at stations around the globe, data collected allows us to make inferences about the structure of Earth. For instance, it can be proven that Earths outer core is liquid, since s-waves are unable to pass through it. Similarly, we know Earth has a solid inner core because some p-waves are reflected off of it. By measuring the time it takes for seismic activity to travel along different paths, the velocity and structure of Earth can be analyzed.\
